comment: Saric (PHI) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Hollis-Jefferson (BKN) makes contact with the ball and any contact with Saric (PHI) is considered incidental.
[Observable in enhanced video] McConnell (PHI) moves his pivot foot.
Covington (PHI) makes marginal contact with Whitehead (BKN) that does not affect his ability to defend the play.
Hollis-Jefferson (BKN) legally contests McConnell's (PHI) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Covington (PHI) makes incidental contact with Whitehead (BKN) during rebounding.
Covington (PHI) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Lin (BKN) that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Lin (BKN) fumbles the ball on the shot attempt and is allowed to retrieve it without taking any additional steps.
Holmes (PHI) firms up his position and sets the screen on Hollis-Jefferson (BKN).
Lopez (BKN) makes incidental contact with Saric (PHI) that does not affect his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] Saric (PHI) moves his pivot foot prior to making the pass.
Lin (BKN) makes contact to the body of McConnell (PHI) prior to the block and the contact affects his shot attempt.
Covington (PHI) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly strips the ball from LeVert (BKN) on his drive to the basket.
Lin (BKN) makes incidental contact with McConnell (PHI) that does not affect his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] McConnell (PHI) slides his pivot foot after the gather.
Holmes (PHI) and Lin (BKN) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Lopez (BKN) and Stauskas (PHI) briefly engage and separate during the inbound.
Saric (PHI) sets the screen on Lopez (BKN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
McConnell (PHI) is awarded the timeout within 5 seconds.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of PHI possession is confirmed.
Whitehead (BKN) commits a take foul on Holmes (PHI).
Hamilton (BKN) sets the screen on Stauskas (PHI) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
